South African Pesident Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to be the first leader to deliver a speech via hologram. Ramaphosa will deliver the keynote speech at the  4th Industrial Revolution SA – Digital Economy Summit at the Gallagher Convention Centre in Midrand on Friday. In a different province is South Africa a hologram of Ramaphosa will be broadcast in real time  at the Rustenburg Civic Centre in North West. A holographic display uses light to give a 3D impression of an image. This means those watching the hologram in North West will  be able to view an image of Ramphosa a though he is physically standing in front of them. [Watch] 4IRSA digital Economic Summit 2019 https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Asxmyf9EvP